==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|ea}}, {{m|enm|eo}} (with spelling influenced by French {{m|fr|eau}}), from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|Ä“a||running water, water, stream, river}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*ahwÅ||waters, river}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*hâ‚‚ekÊ·ehâ‚‚||water, flowing water}}. Compare {{m|en|ea}}, {{m|en|yeo}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{rhymes|É™ÊŠ|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|Lincolnshire|_|toponymy}} A [[brook]] or [[stream]].

===Anagrams===
* {{anagrams|en|U.A.E.|UAE|UEA|Uea}}

