==French==

===Etymology===
From {{inh|fr|frm|[[eau]], [[eaue]]}}, from {{inh|fr|fro|ewe}}, {{m|fro|euwe}}, {{m|fro|egua||water}}, from {{inh|fr|la|aqua||water}}, from {{inh|fr|itc-pro|*akÊ·Ä}}, from {{inh|fr|ine-pro|*hâ‚‚ekÊ·ehâ‚‚||water, flowing water}}. Cognate with {{cog|ang|Ä“a||flowing water, stream, river}}. More at {{m|en|ea}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{fr-IPA}}
* {{audio|Fr-eau.ogg|audio ("de l'eau")|lang=fr}}
* {{rhymes|o|lang=fr}}
* {{homophones|au|aux|aulx|eaux|haut|hauts|ho|o|Ã´|oh|os|lang=fr}}

===Noun===
{{fr-noun|f|eaux}}

# [[water|Water]], a [[liquid]] that is [[transparent]], [[colorless]], [[odorless]]{{,}} and [[tasteless]] in its pure form, the primary constituent of [[lake]]s, [[river]]s, [[sea]]s{{,}} and [[ocean]]s.
