==Dutch==

===Alternative forms===
* {{l|nl|gelove}} {{qual|archaic}}

===Etymology===
From earlier {{m|nl|gelove}}, from {{inh|nl|dum|gelove}}, from {{inh|nl|odt|gilovo}}, from {{inh|nl|gem-pro|*galaubÃ´}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{rhymes|oËf|lang=nl}}
* {{audio|Nl-geloof.ogg|audio|lang=nl}}

===Noun===
{{nl-noun|n|-ven|geloofje}}

# [[belief]], [[conviction]].
# {{lb|nl|religion}} [[faith]], [[religion]].

====Usage notes====
The genitive form of the word is ''des geloofs''. Of its alternative form ''gelove'' it is ''des geloven'' or ''des geloves''. In Dutch, the genitive is not commonly used outside of fixed expressions and literary language, but can be frequently encountered in early modern Dutch texts.

====Synonyms====
* {{sense|belief|conviction}} {{l|nl|overtuiging}}
* {{sense|religion}} {{l|nl|godsdienst}}, {{l|nl|religie}}

====Derived terms====
* {{l|nl|bijgeloof}} {{g2|n}}
